================================
BLOG SYSTEM RULES (CRITICAL)
================================
- Blog must be fully server-rendered
- Dynamic routes via /blog/[slug]
- Content source may be:
  - Headless CMS
  - MDX
  - Static data (abstracted)
- Blog listing page:
  - Indexable
  - Paginated (server-side)
- Blog detail page MUST include:
  - Dynamic metadata
  - Canonical URL
  - BlogPosting JSON-LD
  - Author & publish date
  - Internal links to solutions/features
- Use generateStaticParams + SSG where possible
- Revalidation allowed (ISR)

================================
PERFORMANCE & TECHNICAL SEO
================================
- next/image is mandatory for all images
- next/font for all fonts
- Avoid useEffect, useState, useRef unless required
- No unnecessary client-side hydration
- Prefer static rendering (SSG)
- Use:
  - sitemap.ts (all public routes)
  - robots.ts (SEO-friendly defaults)
- Implement not-found.tsx
- Ensure accessibility:
  - alt texts
  - aria labels where needed
  - keyboard navigability

================================
STYLING & UI CONSISTENCY
================================
- Tailwind utility-first approach
- Mobile-first layouts
- max-w-7xl container pattern
- Consistent spacing scale
- Accessible color contrast (WCAG AA minimum)
- SaaS-style clean UI (no clutter)

================================
WHEN GENERATING ANY PAGE
================================
You MUST:
1. Show the folder structure first
2. Explain the SEO intent of the page (1–2 sentences)
3. Provide full page.tsx code
4. Ensure the page is a Server Component
5. Ensure metadata is correctly defined
6. Ensure headings and content follow SEO rules

================================
ABSOLUTE PROHIBITIONS
================================
- Do NOT default to "use client"
- Do NOT add JavaScript-heavy libraries
- Do NOT skip metadata
- Do NOT reuse titles/descriptions across pages
- Do NOT generate thin content
